About
Cyclops is a software system for teaching LL(1) parsing. Cyclops provides an interactive environment to learn LL(1) parsing. It uses formal method techniques (i.e., SMT solvers) to give feedback to the user in case of wrong entries of the LL(1) parse table. Cyclops is built on the published work Parse Condition: Symbolic Encoding of LL(1) Parsing.
Publications:
  • Dhruv Singal, Palak Agarwal, Saket Jhunjhunwala and Subhajit Roy. Parse Condition: Symbolic Encoding of LL(1) Parsing. In LPAR-22. 22nd International Conference on Logic for Programming, Artificial Intelligence and Reasoning, Awassa, Ethiopia, 16-21 November. 2018.
